nodes.documentation:
@title Basic Fundraiser


@dev An abstract contract that is a base for fundraisers. 
It implements a generic procedure for handling received funds:
1. Validates the transaciton preconditions
2. Calculates the amount of tokens based on the conversion rate.
3. Delegate the handling of the tokens (mint, transfer or conjure)
4. Delegate the handling of the funds
5. Emit event for received funds
nodes.name: BasicFundraiser

allowance(address,address).details: Checks the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender.

params._owner: The address which owns the funds allowed for spending by a third-party.
params._spender: The third-party address that is allowed to spend the tokens.

allowance(address,address).return: The number of tokens available to `_spender` to be spent.

approve(address,uint256).details: Give permission to `_spender` to spend `_value` number of tokens on your behalf. E.g. You place a buy or sell order on an exchange and in that example, the  `_spender` address is the address of the contract the exchange created to add your token to their  website and you are `msg.sender`.

params._spender: The address which will spend the funds.
params._value: The amount of tokens to be spent.

approve(address,uint256).return: Whether the approval process was successful or not.

balanceOf(address).details: Get the balance of an address.

params._address: The address which's balance will be checked.

balanceOf(address).return: The current balance of the address.

transfer(address,uint256).details: Transfers `_value` number of tokens to the `_to` address.

params._value: The number of tokens to be transferred.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Allows another contract to spend tokens on behalf of the `_from` address and send them to the `_to` address.

params._from: The address which approved you to spend tokens on their behalf.
params._to: The address where you want to send tokens.
params._value: The number of tokens to be sent.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).return: Whether the transfer was successful or not.
